Package au.csiro.pathling.fhirpath.function

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    NamedFunction
    Represents a named function in FHIRPath.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AggregateFunction
    Represents a function intended to reduce a set of values to a single value.
    BooleansTestFunction  
    CountFunction
    A function for aggregating data based on counting the number of rows within the result.
    EmptyFunction
    This function returns true if the input collection is empty.
    ExistsFunction
    A function which is able to test whether the input collection is empty.
    ExtensionFunction
    A function that returns the extensions of the current element that match a given url.
    FirstFunction
    This function allows the selection of only the first element of a collection.
    IifFunction
    This function takes three arguments, Returns the second argument if the first argument evaluates to true, or the third argument otherwise.
    NamedFunctionInput
    Represents the inputs to a named function in FHIRPath.
    NotFunction
    Returns true if the input collection evaluates to false, and false if it evaluates to true.
    OfTypeFunction
    A function filters items in the input collection to only those that are of the given type.
    ResolveFunction
    A function for resolving a Reference element in order to access the elements of the target resource.
    ReverseResolveFunction
    A function for accessing elements of resources which refer to the input resource.
    SumFunction
    A function for computing the sum of a collection of numeric values.
    UntilFunction
    This function computes the time interval (duration) between two paths representing dates or dates with time.
    Validations
    Provides a home for common validation code used by functions.
    WhereFunction
    Describes a function which can scope down the previous invocation within a FHIRPath expression, based upon an expression passed in as an argument.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    BooleansTestFunction.BooleansTestType
    Represents a type of test that can be performed against a collection of Boolean values.
